Board of DirectorsDeep experience in resource industry in South America


The Board consists of exploration professionals that have an enviable track record of mineral discoveries blended with entrepreneurs and seasoned business leaders that have raised over $2.5 billion in financing for resource companies and have been involved in numerous mergers and acquisitions totalling over $15 billion in value.


Dr. Keith M. Barron, B.Sc., Ph.D Founder, Chair of the Safety, Health, Environment, Community and Technical Committee- Founded Aurelian Resources & discovered the 13 million ounce Fruta del Norte gold deposit in Ecuador. Aurelian was sold to Kinross Gold for $1.2 billion.
- Owner & operator of private mine that is the USA’s only commercial sapphire producer, along with gold from gravel that is similar to the host of uranium and vanadium at U3O8 Corp.’s Laguna Salada Deposit in Argentina.
- Recipient of PDAC’s Thayer Lindsley International Discovery Award – 2008
- Northern Miner’s Mining Man of the Year – 2008
U3O8 Corp
Mr. David Constable, BSc, MBA, ICD.DChairman of the Board- Involved in eight M&A transactions with a total value of $10 billion including the sale of Australia’s Normandy Mining to Newmont; the merger of FNX Mining with Quadra Resources; the sale of Gold Eagle Mines to Goldcorp; and the sale of Aquiline Resources to Pan American Silver after the discovery of the massive Navidad silver deposit in Argentina;
- Headed up Investor Relations (IR) at Normandy Mining & subsequently at Toronto-based FNX Mining during the discoveries in Sudbury that took the Company from junior explorer to a producer with a multi-billion dollar market cap;
- Holds a ICD.D designation from Institute of Canadian Directors.
U3O8 Corp
Mr. David Franklin, MBAChair of Audit Committee - Co-founder, and is Managing Director of WoodsWater Capital LP, a resource-focused private equity firm;
- Formerly CEO of Sprott Private Wealth;
- Was market strategist at Sprott where he co-wrote the widely-followed monthly note “Markets at a Glace” with Eric Sprott;
- Has put together numerous M&A deals.
U3O8 Corp
Mr. Pablo Marcet, BSc, MSc, MBAChair of the Compensation, Corporate Governance and Nominating Committee- Involved in the start-up the giant Escondida copper mine in Chile;
- As President of Northern Orion, oversaw advancement of the Agua Rica copper-gold porphyry deposit towards development in Argentina and subsequent takeover of Northern Orion by Yamana Gold for $1.6 billion;
- Was President of Waymar Resources which made a gold discovery in Colombia and subsequently merged with Orosur Mining that has an operating gold mine in Uruguay;
- Pablo lives in Argentina.
U3O8 Corp
Mr. Darin Milmeister, B.Sc (Business Admin)Director- Graduate of Georgetown University - B.Sc in Business Administration, Finance & Accounting;
- Initially was with Deutsche Bank in leveraged finance;
- Was a principal of Delaware Street Capital managing long/short fund focused on basic materials; &
- Currently founder & Managing Partner of Extract Capital – a resource-focused fund
U3O8 CorpDr. Richard Spencer, BSc(Hons), PhD, CGeol, PGeoDirector, President and CEO- Target generation & exploration of the giant gold-uranium deposits of the Witwatersrand Basin in South Africa;
- Led the exploration teams that:
• Discovered the 3.3 million ounce Quimsacocha / Loma Larga gold deposit in Ecuador (also contains 23 million ounces of silver);
• Increased the gold reserve at the Las Cristinas deposit in Venezuela by 65% from 10.2 million ounces to 16.8 million ounces;
• Discovered a belt of porphyry copper deposits in Ecuador. Resources are: 23 billion pounds of copper & 4 million ounces of gold in the Mirador, Panantza & San Carlos deposits.
